                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>ایلخانی</p>
                     <p>زيج</p>
                     <p>Zij-i-khant (or Khání, as it is here entitled), containing the Astronomical <lb/>
Tables constructed by Naşiru'd-Din Túsí by command of Hulákú Khán the <lb/>
Mongol. See Rieu's Persian Catalogue, pp. 454-455, and Brockelmann's Gesch. d. <lb/>
Arab. Litt., vol. 1, pp. 511-512.</p>
                     <p>This beautiful little MS., obtained from the late Hájjí 'Abdu'l-Majid Belshah <lb/>
in January, 1920, is not dated, but was probably transcribed in the fifteenth century <lb/>
of our era. It comprises 148 ff. of 17'2 x 12'5 c. and 19 ll., and is written in a small, <lb/>
neat naskh with rubrications and many Tables (ff. 27-93, 99-118", etc.). Of the <lb/>
four Discourses (Maqála) into which it is divided, of which the subjects are given <lb/>
by Rieu, the first begins on f. 3", the second on f. 20%, the third on f. 93%, and the <lb/>
fourth on f. 137".</p>
                  </summary>
